# 🔐 Caesar Cipher Project

A Python-based Caesar Cipher application that allows users to encrypt and decrypt messages by shifting
characters in the alphabet.

## 🚀 Features

* Encrypt Messages
* Decrypt Messages
* Custom Shift Value
* Handles Spaces and Special Characters
* Input Validation
* Repeat Operations Without Restarting the Program
* User-Friendly Console Interface


## 🎯 Learning Outcomes

Through this project, I learned:

* How encryption algorithms work
* Function creation and parameter passing
* String processing techniques
* Error handling using try-except
* Building interactive command-line applications
* Using modulus operator for circular indexing

## 🔮 Future Improvements

* Support for uppercase letters
* Save encrypted messages to a file
* GUI version using Tkinter
* Random key generation
* Multiple encryption algorithms








